Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals marked proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or acute/chronic kidney injury with tubular dysfunction. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
